var is function scoped and gets hoisted and is able to be redclared, let cannot be redeclared, is not hoisted and is block scoped.
var is function scoped and gets hoisted and is able to be redclared, const cannot be redeclared, is not hoisted and is block scoped
let can be reassiged const cannot
hoisting is when a variable declaration is processed before initialization allowing the variable to be accessed prior to
intilization returning undefined.
